# STRICT ALLOWLIST. `*` ignores everything; only the paths the Dockerfile COPYs are
# re-included. MAINTENANCE RULE: every `COPY <src>` in the Dockerfile MUST have a matching
# `!<src>` line here, or the build fails with "file not found". Update both together.
*

# --- re-include exactly what the Dockerfile needs ---
!pyproject.toml
!backend
!frontend

# --- strip cruft from inside the re-included trees (last match wins) ---
**/__pycache__
**/*.py[cod]
frontend/node_modules
frontend/dist
frontend/coverage
# NOTE: backend/static is intentionally KEPT (do not exclude) — see RESEARCH Pitfall 6.
# The wheel's package-data needs it; the multi-stage build overwrites the served copy anyway.
